        <abstract>
            <p>Thanks for the monoecious hop. It was the first monstrosity he ever observed.</p> 
<p>Contemplates an article in <hi rend="italic">Gardeners’ Chronicle</hi> on the horticultural bearing of CD’s fertilisation work.</p>  
<p>Will publish note forwarded by CD on a male hop with apparently female flowers (<hi rend="italic">Gardeners’ Chronicle</hi>, 8 August 1874, p. 174). </p> 
        </abstract>
